title: Matt Talbert’s CV
text:
Computer Scientist, Data Scientist and Student.

tal21005@byui.edu | My LinkedIn Page



Studying at BYUi


Data Science, Mobile Development, Web Design.



Data Analyticts, Artificial Intelligence.




2017-2021 West Lafayette, Jr/Sr High School
September 2023 - now Brigham Young University - Idaho 



January 2024 - Present Assistant Curriculum Designer, Brigham Young University Idaho Rexburg, ID

Curated and published content for a variety of online college-level courses
Coded dynamic course instructional pages with both CSS and HTML

September 2023 - December 2023 STC Early Morning Custodian, Brigham Young University Idaho Rexburg, ID

Committed to a rigorous 4:30am-7:30am schedule while balancing responsibilities of higher education
Coordinated to fulfill individual and group cleaning deadlines

July 2023 - September 2023 Seasonal Front End Associate, Target Lafayette, IN

Developed advanced soft skills working at the customer service des
Worked overtime reaching +50 hours a week during the busy, back to school season

May 2021 - July 2021 Garden Center Associate, Ace Hardware West Lafayette, IN

Demonstrated soft skills working with customers and coworkers in a fast paced environment
Led a department of the store by managing sales, restocking and product care and mantainence

March 2020 - March 2021 Front End Associate, Kroger Stores West Lafayette, IN

Varied experience in fulfilling online orders, front end cleaning/sorting and utility clerk responsibilities
Over 600 hours working both as an individual and as a part of a large team




July 2021 - July 2023 Full Time Missionary, the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints Fort Collins, CO

Over 6,500 hours spent studying, planning, meeting and teaching
Spoke Spanish with native speakers for 2 years
Spent several months training several new missionaries one on one
Was responsible for motivating, training, reporting the progress of and caring for up to 22 other missionaries at a time in leadership positions
Taught English to non-english speakers in weekly classes
